President Biden was asked several questions during a press conference on the South Lawn. He was asked about the need for another U.S.-Russia summit, to which he responded that they will be talking at length. He was also questioned about his responsibility regarding the 800,000 coronavirus deaths and why he hasn't asked China to be more transparent about the origins of the virus. President Biden expressed hope that the Build Back Better Act will be passed this year but acknowledged that it will be a close call. When asked about Congress holding Mark Meadows in contempt, he stated that he hasn't spoken to anyone about it but believes it is worthy of contempt. The President admitted that he hasn't seen all the texts that have been released. Lastly, he mentioned that there has been some progress made on the Build Back Better Act.